<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Become a Kurd</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="joint">Lots of people become Kurds</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1002" relname="joint">and this will give you some tips and tricks onbecoming one .</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="5" relname="attribution">Be aware</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1004" relname="span">that becoming a Kurd is not for the faint-hearted .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1003" relname="joint">Do not become a Kurd just for the &quot; good bits &quot; .</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1007" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1007" relname="joint">Decide what kind of Kurd you want to be .</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1007" relname="joint">There are Turkish Kurds , Syrian Kurds , Iraqi Kurds , Iranian Kurds , Sorani Kurds , Kurmanji Kurds and Hawrami Kurds .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1010" relname="contrast">Do some internet research</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1011" relname="span">or find a book about Kurds at a library or bookstore</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="11" relname="purpose">to help make this decision .</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1013" relname="span">One should only become the kind of Kurd</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="13" relname="elaboration">they can relate to the most .</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1015" relname="preparation">Adhere to the religion .</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1016" relname="span">Some 90 % of Kurds are Sunni Muslims</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="16" relname="elaboration">following the Shafi legal code .</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1019" relname="span">Luckily , conversion to Islam is very easy ,</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="18" relname="elaboration">one just needs to declare their faith , either to themselves or officially in a mosque .</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1021" relname="joint">The other 10 % are Yazidis , Yarsanis and Alevis .</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1023" relname="concession">While it is difficult to convert to Yazidism ,</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1023" relname="joint">Yarsanism and Alevism are much more accepting of converts</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="24" relname="condition">and if you live in a big city ,</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1024" relname="span">you should be able to find a Cemevi or a Yarsani temple .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1027" relname="span">Most Kurds focus more on being Kurds</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="25" relname="antithesis">than being religious ,</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="contrast">so you do n&apos;t need to be overly religious</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1028" relname="contrast">or take part in all the religious rituals .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1026" relname="elaboration">It &apos;s more about being part of the group than anything else .</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1017" relname="joint">Change your name .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1031" relname="span">Usually you can legally change your name</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="33" relname="condition">if you are 18 ,</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1032" relname="span">but it depends where you live .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1035" relname="condition">If you are a Turkish Kurd ,</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1035" relname="span">you should choose a Kurdish first name and Turkish surname</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="35" relname="circumstance">as Kurdish surnames are banned in Turkey .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1038" relname="condition">If you are an Iraqi Kurd ,</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1038" relname="sequence">choose a Kurdish first name , a religious male middle name and surname ,</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1038" relname="sequence">and then a tribal or geographical designator .</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="41" relname="condition">If you are an Iranian Kurd ,</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1040" relname="span">choose a Kurdish first name and an Iranian surname .</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1042" relname="joint">Dress</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1042" relname="joint">and look like a Kurd .</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1044" relname="span">This does not mean</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1045" relname="span">wearing traditional garb all the time ,</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1048" relname="span">even though it is a wise idea</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="46" relname="purpose">to have a brown or olive green suit</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1048" relname="elaboration">( for men )</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1049" relname="span">or a dress</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="49" relname="elaboration">( for women ) .</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1043" relname="joint">You can buy these from online stores , Ebay , and specialist shops .</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1052" relname="joint">Kurdish girls wear heavy makeup</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1052" relname="joint">and have thick eyebrows and long lashes .</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="55" relname="condition">If you are female ,</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1055" relname="span">invest in some eyebrow pencil , foundation and mascara ,</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1054" relname="contrast">or get your eyebrows tinted .</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1058" relname="condition">If you are female</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="59" relname="condition">and you are an Iraqi Kurd or Iranian Kurd ,</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1058" relname="span">you might be expected to put a scarf over most of your hair .</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1053" relname="joint">It should be stylish , possibly designer .</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1053" relname="joint">Do n&apos;t forget the oversized sunglasses .</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1063" relname="condition">If you are male ,</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1063" relname="joint">wear baggy jeans , sports clothes , cologne or perfume ,</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1063" relname="joint">and always be clean-shaven .</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1065" relname="preparation">Try to learn the lingo .</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1066" relname="preparation">While textbooks and online resources</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1067" relname="preparation">for learning Kurdish are limited ,</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1068" relname="contrast">it is possible to find a private tutor</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1069" relname="span">or go to a group language learning class ,</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="69" relname="condition">if you live in a European city .</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="72" relname="condition">If you live in a Midwestern hick town ,</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1071" relname="span">you &apos;re out of luck .</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1074" relname="concession">This is n&apos;t mandatory ,</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1074" relname="span">but it is recommended that learn a third language</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="74" relname="elaboration">depending on what kind of Kurd you are .</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="1076" relname="span">An Iranian Kurd would learn Farsi ,</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1077" relname="joint">an Iraqi Kurd would learn Arabic ,</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1077" relname="joint">and a Turkish Kurd would learn Turkish .</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="80" relname="condition">If you have a knack for languages ,</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="1080" relname="span">why not learn all three ?</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1080" relname="evaluation">Resources for these are much more abundant .</segment>
<segment id="82" parent="1082" relname="preparation">Meet other Kurds .</segment>
<segment id="83" parent="1083" relname="preparation">Join the community .</segment>
<segment id="84" parent="1084" relname="span">The aforementioned cities , like London , Paris and Berlin , should have Kurdish community centres</segment>
<segment id="85" parent="84" relname="elaboration">where you can attend meetings , celebrations , commemorations , and protests .</segment>
<segment id="86" parent="1083" relname="joint">Meeting other Kurds can also help with learning the language</segment>
<segment id="87" parent="1083" relname="joint">and finding love .</segment>
<segment id="88" parent="1083" relname="joint">It is better for Kurds to marry other Kurds .</segment>
<segment id="89" parent="1089" relname="preparation">Be prepared to go to lots of protests .</segment>
<segment id="90" parent="1090" relname="span">Making signs and banners is a great way</segment>
<segment id="91" parent="90" relname="purpose">to bond with new friends .</segment>
<segment id="92" parent="1092" relname="preparation">Just stay safe !</segment>
<segment id="93" parent="1092" relname="joint">Protests , especially at night , can be dangerous for young people on their own</segment>
<segment id="94" parent="1094" relname="span">and could even get you arrested</segment>
<segment id="95" parent="94" relname="purpose">so make sure you stay in a group .</segment>
<segment id="96" parent="1096" relname="preparation">Get official documentation .</segment>
<segment id="97" parent="1097" relname="contrast">Sadly , there is no such thing as a &quot; Kurdish passport &quot;</segment>
<segment id="98" parent="1097" relname="contrast">but you can apply for an Iranian , Iraqi , or Turkish passport , and an ID card in Iraq and Turkey .</segment>
<segment id="99" parent="1099" relname="span">If you have a passport</segment>
<segment id="100" parent="1100" relname="same_unit">that might make travelling to the Homeland difficult , like an American passport</segment>
<segment id="101" parent="102" relname="condition">if you are an Iranian Kurd ,</segment>
<segment id="102" parent="1101" relname="span">that and your American citizenship might need to be renounced .</segment>
<segment id="103" parent="1103" relname="preparation">Consider marriage .</segment>
<segment id="104" parent="1105" relname="span">Marrying an Iranian citizen</segment>
<segment id="105" parent="104" relname="elaboration">( hopefully a Kurd )</segment>
<segment id="106" parent="1104" relname="same_unit">will automatically give you Iranian citizenship .</segment>
<segment id="107" parent="1103" relname="joint">Develop your political views .</segment>
<segment id="108" parent="109" relname="attribution">Keep in mind</segment>
<segment id="109" parent="1108" relname="span">that Kurdish people talk politics as often as English people talk weather .</segment>
<segment id="110" parent="111" relname="condition">If you are a Turkish Kurd ,</segment>
<segment id="111" parent="1110" relname="span">you would probably support the left-wing HDP .</segment>
<segment id="112" parent="1103" relname="joint">The leader is currently imprisoned .</segment>
<segment id="113" parent="1103" relname="joint">Disagreement with Erdogan is de rigueur .</segment>
<segment id="114" parent="1103" relname="joint">Campaign for your basic human rights .</segment>
<segment id="115" parent="116" relname="condition">If you are an Iraqi Kurd ,</segment>
<segment id="116" parent="1116" relname="span">you already have a semi-autonomous jurisdiction ... and a problem with nepotism and corruption ,</segment>
<segment id="117" parent="1115" relname="span">so you would show a certain amount of distrust of the local govt. Campaign for further independence .</segment>
<segment id="118" parent="119" relname="condition">If you are an Iranian Kurd ,</segment>
<segment id="119" parent="1119" relname="span">you would generally not vote ,</segment>
<segment id="120" parent="1118" relname="span">having similar distrust for the govt. Campaign for the abolition of the death penalty .</segment>
<segment id="121" parent="1121" relname="preparation">Prepare to confront haters .</segment>
<segment id="122" parent="1122" relname="span">Sadly , even in this day and age , many people wo n&apos;t respect your decision</segment>
<segment id="123" parent="1123" relname="span">to live as a Kurd</segment>
<segment id="124" parent="123" relname="purpose">so you need to be able to discuss it with them in a civilised way .</segment>
<segment id="125" parent="1125" relname="span">Do n&apos;t be overly zealous with people</segment>
<segment id="126" parent="125" relname="elaboration">who might not be sympathetic .</segment>
<segment id="127" parent="1121" relname="joint">Some subjects are only suitable for discussion with other Kurds .</segment>
<segment id="128" parent="1121" relname="joint">Be articulate and confident .</segment>
<segment id="129" parent="1129" relname="span">You can practice this</segment>
<segment id="130" parent="129" relname="means">by joining a debate club , Model Un , or toastmasters .</segment>
<segment id="131" parent="1121" relname="joint">Be prepared to be called &quot; other &quot; and &quot; enemy &quot; and &quot; terrorist &quot; .</segment>
<segment id="132" parent="1131" relname="span">This may be distressing</segment>
<segment id="133" parent="1132" relname="same_unit">so it helps</segment>
<segment id="134" parent="135" relname="condition">if you consistently tell yourself</segment>
<segment id="135" parent="1133" relname="span">that you are n&apos;t .</segment>
